A '''clearing account''' is usually a temporary account containing costs or amounts that are to be transferred to another account. An example is the income summary account containing [[revenue]] and [[expense]] amounts to be transferred to [[retained earnings]] at the close of a fiscal period.<ref>http://www.businessdictionary.com/definition/clearing-account.html</ref>

Other example of clearing account is excise clearing account.

